{
  "texts": [
    "Extended capabilities are built to provide anomaly detection for a time-series window of sensor readings tending towards the boundaries or around the centre of the probability distribution (see Fig. 12).",
    "Stealth attacks on ICS were studied in Urbina et al [24].",
    "The goal of an adversary is to keep detection statistic below the selected threshold.",
    "Some detection solutions using a residual-error threshold [13] are vulnerable to stealth attacks.",
    "We used stateful detection to catch anomalies based on the probability distribution of state values in a time-window."
  ]
}